## Summary

A compass rose shows 16 directions. The four main ones are **north (N), south (S), east (E),** and **west (W)**, at 90-degree intervals.

The four **intercardinal** directions are **northeast (NE), southeast (SE), southwest (SW),** and **northwest (NW)**.

The remaining eight directions are in between these, called **secondary intercardinal** directions. These directions can also be described using azimuth angles.
title: Cardinal direction
